{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":368432,"duration_api_ms":344174,"num_turns":45,"result":"```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"ExecutionPayload/v1\",\n  \"project_id\": \"gn8\",\n  \"stage\": \"plan_and_implement\",\n  \"cycle\": 1,\n  \"completion_round\": 16,\n  \"status\": \"amendments_applied\",\n  \"amendments_received\": 3,\n  \"amendments_applied\": 3,\n  \"amendments_deferred\": 0,\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"src/adapters/process_backend.rs\",\n      \"description\": \"Added signal-kill warning logging in classify_exit_failure: on Unix, when status.code() is None (signal kill), extracts the signal number via status.signal() and emits a tracing::warn with the signal number. Retry behaviour unchanged (still TransportFailure). Refactored the match to distinguish Some(127), Some(_), and None arms explicitly.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs\",\n      \"description\": \"Changed pre-backoff snapshot write from `let _ = run_snapshot_write.write_run_snapshot(...)` to propagate the error via `?`. If the snapshot write fails, the run aborts immediately instead of silently continuing into a backoff that cannot be crash-recovered.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs\",\n      \"description\": \"Fixed derive_resume_state to preserve retry-attempt state across crash. Added a HashMap tracking the highest retryable-failed attempt per (stage_id, cycle) from StageFailed journal events with will_retry=true. The resume cursor now starts at failed_attempt+1 instead of hardcoded 1, preventing retry budget replenishment on restart during the backoff window.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"tests\": \"683 passed, 0 failed\",\n    \"clippy\": \"clean (0 warnings)\",\n    \"fmt\": \"clean (no formatting differences)\"\n  },\n  \"notes\": \"Amendment 1 uses cfg(unix) gating for the signal() call; on non-Unix platforms the None arm still returns TransportFailure without logging. Amendment 2 matches the pattern used in fail_run() which also propagates snapshot write errors via ?. Amendment 3 only tracks will_retry=true failures since terminal failures (will_retry=false) indicate the run should not resume at the next attempt.\"\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":2.4345777499999994,"usage":{"input_tokens":27,"cache_creation_input_tokens":56324,"cache_read_input_tokens":1239025,"output_tokens":12067,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":56324,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":28074,"outputTokens":17742,"cacheReadInputTokens":1250328,"cacheCreationInputTokens":196079,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.4345777499999994,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"06108048-f67d-4fb7-86b2-8b9913d890e9"}
